  "prompt": "International awards of Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has received numerous international awards and honors for his contributions to the Indian film industry and beyond. Here are some of the notable international awards and recognitions he has received:\n\n1. **Legion of Honour (France)**:\n   - In 2014, Shah Rukh Khan was awarded the Legion of Honour, France\u2019s highest civilian award, by the French government for his outstanding contributions to the world of cinema.\n\n2. **World Economic Forum Crystal Award (Switzerland)**:\n   - In 2018, Shah Rukh Khan received the Crystal Award at the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, for his leadership in championing women\u2019s and children\u2019s rights in India.\n\n3. **UNESCO Pyramide con Marni Award (Italy)**:\n   - In 2011, Shah Rukh Khan was honored with the UNESCO Pyramide con Marni Award for his commitment to promoting education for underprivileged children.\n\n4. **Asian Film Awards (Hong Kong)**:\n   - Shah Rukh Khan has been honored multiple times at the Asian Film Awards, including the Lifetime Achievement Award in 2018.\n\n5. **Knight of the Order of Arts and Letters (France)**:\n   - In 2007, Shah Rukh Khan was awarded the Knight of the Order of Arts and Letters (Chevalier des Arts et des Lettres) by the French government for his contributions to arts and cinema.\n\n6. **Honorary Doctorate from the University of Edinburgh (UK)**:\n   - In 2015, Shah Rukh Khan was awarded an honorary doctorate in arts and culture by the University of Edinburgh, Scotland, for his achievements in the film industry and his philanthropic efforts.\n\n7. **Honorary Doctorate from the University of Law and Economy (Bulgaria)**:\n   - In 2011, he received an honorary doctorate from the University of Law and Economy in Bulgaria for his contributions to global cinema.\n\n8. **Global Diversity Award (UK)**:\n   - In 2008, Shah Rukh Khan received the Global Diversity Award at the House of Commons in London for his work promoting diversity in the entertainment industry.\n\n9. **Honorary Doctorate from the University of Bedfordshire (UK)**:\n   - In 2009, Shah Rukh Khan was awarded an honorary doctorate by the University of Bedfordshire for his contributions to the arts and his philanthropic work.\n\n10. **Asian Achievers Awards (UK)**:\n    - In 2017, Shah Rukh Khan was honored at the Asian Achievers Awards in London for his outstanding contributions to the world of cinema.\n\nThese awards and recognitions highlight Shah Rukh Khan's global influence and his dedication to philanthropy, education, and the arts.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
